  "prompt": "What are some examples of capital-intensive industries?",
  "response": "Capital-intensive industries are those that require large amounts of capital investment in machinery, equipment, and facilities to produce goods or services. Examples of such industries include:\n\n1. **Automobile Manufacturing:** This industry involves significant investments in production plants, machinery, and technology to produce vehicles. \n\n2. **Oil and Gas:** Exploration, extraction, refining, and distribution of oil and gas require substantial infrastructure, equipment, and technology.\n\n3. **Aerospace:** The design, production, and maintenance of aircraft and spacecraft involve high capital costs due to expensive materials, sophisticated equipment, and advanced technology.\n\n4. **Telecommunications:** Building and maintaining networks, satellites, and other communication infrastructure require substantial financial investments.\n\n5. **Utilities:** Production and distribution of electricity, water, and other utilities demand large-scale infrastructure such as power plants, transmission lines, and water treatment facilities.\n\n6. **Mining:** Extracting minerals and ores from the earth requires expensive machinery, extraction technologies, and facilities for processing and refinement.\n\n7. **Pharmaceuticals:** Research, development, and manufacturing of drugs involve heavy investments in specialized equipment, laboratories, and regulatory compliance.\n\n8. **Railroads:** Construction and maintenance of tracks, trains, and stations require significant capital investment.\n\n9. **Semiconductor Manufacturing:** Production of semiconductor chips involves specialized machinery and cleanroom facilities with high capital costs.\n\n10. **Shipping and Logistics:** Investment in vessels, port infrastructure, and warehouse facilities is substantial for maritime and freight logistics industries.\n\nThese industries typically have high fixed costs and require ongoing investments to maintain competitive advantage and operational efficiency.",
